WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.463 --> 00:00:02.577
The VISN chief supply chain officer

2
00:00:02.577 --> 00:00:05.593
works with clinical groups to meet patient care needs

3
00:00:05.593 --> 00:00:07.662
while seeking ways to achieve supply chain goals

4
00:00:07.662 --> 00:00:10.360
such as assisting with the formulation

5
00:00:10.360 --> 00:00:13.662
of VHA/SCM policies and procedures.

6
00:00:13.662 --> 00:00:16.883
Other responsibilities include establishing communication

7
00:00:16.883 --> 00:00:19.941
with VA medical facilities to effectively implement

8
00:00:19.941 --> 00:00:23.390
SCM policy, reporting, training,

9
00:00:23.390 --> 00:00:26.525
and operational requirements, as well as assessing

10
00:00:26.525 --> 00:00:29.992
inventory management programs at VISN medical facilities

11
00:00:29.992 --> 00:00:33.529
through quality control review once per fiscal year.

12
00:00:33.529 --> 00:00:36.081
Additional duties include insuring compliance

13
00:00:36.081 --> 00:00:38.975
with established VA and VHA directives,

14
00:00:38.975 --> 00:00:42.955
handbooks, memoranda, notices, and managing

15
00:00:42.955 --> 00:00:46.013
supply chain data in coordination with the facility

16
00:00:46.013 --> 00:00:48.763
chief logistics officer, or FCLO.

